  "prompt": "Who is the Necromancer in The Hobbit?",
  "response": "In J.R.R. Tolkien's \"The Hobbit,\" the Necromancer is a dark and mysterious figure who resides in the fortress of Dol Guldur in Mirkwood. The Necromancer is later revealed to be Sauron, the primary antagonist of Tolkien's subsequent work, \"The Lord of the Rings.\" Sauron's presence in Mirkwood is a sign of his growing power and the threat he poses to Middle-earth. While the Necromancer plays a relatively minor role in \"The Hobbit,\" his influence and the danger he represents are expanded upon in \"The Lord of the Rings\" and other related writings by Tolkien.",
